Antonovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Oktyabrsky Rural Okrug of Nyurbinsky District in the Sakha Republic, Russia, located  from Nyurba, the administrative center of the district. Its population as of the 2010 Census was 2,642; up from 2,514 recorded in the 2002 Census.
